## Appendix: Legal References

### Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA)

**15 U.S.C. § 1681c(a) - Information Excluded from Consumer Reports**
> Negative information cannot be reported more than 7 years from the date of first delinquency.

**15 U.S.C. § 1681e(b) - Accuracy Requirements**
> Consumer reporting agencies must follow reasonable procedures to assure maximum possible accuracy.

**15 U.S.C. § 1681s-2(a) - Furnisher Duties**
> Furnishers must not report information known or believed to be inaccurate.

**15 U.S.C. § 1681i - Dispute Reinvestigation**
> Bureaus must investigate disputes within 30 days and correct or delete inaccurate information.

### Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (FDCPA)

**15 U.S.C. § 1692e - False Representations**
> Debt collectors may not use false, deceptive, or misleading representations.

